source: Autor: Mária Rušínová
translation: Article summary: AI-powered machine translation technology is present in our lives and has revolutionized the way we communicate. It has transformed the global trading of language barriers by enabling people to access information and understand each other regardless of language differences. This technology has gained huge momentum in the field of translation and interpretation, and its impact has been witnessed in almost every industry sector today. From educational textbooks to political speeches, AI-powered translation software has been integrated into almost all forms of communication. One of the prominent applications of machine translation technology is in helping website operators to offer multilingual contents. In such a scenario, Google Translate emerged as the most commonly used online translation tool in the world. This tool allows users to translate content from one language to another, and it is praised by users due to the accuracy of the translations it provides. Moreover, human language also features complexities which cannot be easily translated by machines, and it requires human intervention to make translations more accurate. This is when MT post-editing (MTPE) comes into play. Machine translation and post-editing (MTPE) is the process of making translations generated via machine translation more accurate and appealing to human readers. It involves a skilled human translator to review and enhance the text generated automatically by software. The post-editing process helps in making the text more readable, natural-sounding, and faithful to the original meaning. In summary, AI-powered machine translation technology has enabled people to break language barriers and communicate seamlessly. This technology has revolutionized the translation industry, and its impact can be seen in almost every industry sector today. Websites run by translation companies are now offering multilingual content and using translation techniques that use human intervention as well as machine translation.
reference: Авто: Марія Рушінова
